 Timothy Eli Thompson was born premature on March 4 without any nasal passages or sinus cavities , a condition so rare it only has a one in 197 million chance of happening .
His mother Brandi McGlathery said Facebook removed a photo of her son a pro-life group tried to post to promote his story .
Doctors hope to be able to drill nasal passages in Eli 's skull when he 's older which will allow him to breathe .